@*
    Phase 3.5 (docs/proposals/openfga.md §3 step 9). When a routed Blazor page
    requires a named policy the (authenticated) user does not satisfy, this
    component performs a real HTTP redirect to the server-rendered
    /access-denied page. Distinct from RedirectToLogin so authenticated-but-
    unauthorized users do not round-trip through /login (which would re-issue
    their existing cookie and loop straight back to the page that just denied
    them). forceLoad: true follows the same rationale as RedirectToLogin —
    /access-denied is server-rendered, not interactive Blazor.
*@
@inject NavigationManager Navigation

@code {
    /// <inheritdoc />
    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        Navigation.NavigateTo("access-denied", forceLoad: true);
    }
}
